After his evacuation of the island, Britain was neglected under the Emperors Augustus and Tiberius. Caligula formed a design of entering Britain, but it ended in nothing. A son of Cyno- bellin, a British chief, expelled by his father, betook himself to the emperor. Caligula, harbouring the fugitive, and receiving him under his protection, wrote boastful despatches to the Senate at Rome, professing to have conquered the entire country.
